<span style="background-color: rgb(186, 186, 255); font-family: monospace; font-weight: bold">[hide param="2.3 (Illegal use of website)"]<br />
Illegal use of our website is typically defined as using our website for commercial or business related purposes without written consent. This is a matter that should be addressed with Lovinity rather than handled yourself.</span><br />
[/hide]<br />
[hide param="2.4 (Editing material against the terms)"]Due to the permissions system in place on the website, this rule should be very hard to violate. Typically speaking, the only people who would violate this are untrustworthy staff. Thus, these violations should be brought up with Lovinity.<br />
[/hide]
<br />
[hide param="3.1 (Breaching website security or integrity)"]This is a zero-tolerance rule and thus in most instances, a&nbsp;<b><span style=" color: #FF0000; ">PERMA-BAN</span></b>&nbsp;should be issued. Reason for this rule should be obvious. The website needs to be stable and secure for our community to enjoy it.<br />
[/hide]
<br />
[hide param="3.2, 8.3, 8.17 (giving false information / gossip)"]<b>When to discipline:</b>&nbsp;If the misinformation is no cause for problems, then no need to discipline&hellip; maybe just let the user know their information is a little off.<br />
<br />
<b>Why we have this rule:</b>&nbsp;Having accurate information is best for a self-help community like this one. In addition, correct information for the staff is a must for being able to accurately and fairly handle reports and other matters. And finally, gossip serves no benefit and simply causes un-needed drama and falsely-damaged reputations.<br />
<br />
In a typical situation, this rule is violated when a member provides staff with false information when staff ask for such information, such as to investigate reports.
