<span style="font-family: Open Sans, Segoe UI, Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #2a212d; ">I&#39;m (your name), (staff position). This is a notice of violation of our website rules, located at http://lovinity.org/pg/rules . Your content, (post a direct link, post number included if forum reply), violates section (section number) of our rules, which states (insert direct quote from the rules). &nbsp;The reason we have this rule is because (explain).</span><br />
<br />
<span style="font-family: Open Sans, Segoe UI, Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #2a212d; ">In an effort to promote corrective behaviour and to remove problematic content from our website, the following disciplinary actions have been taken as a result of your violation:</span></span></p>
<span style="background-color: rgb(186, 186, 255); font-family: monospace; font-weight: bold"> </span>

<ul>
	<li>
	<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; orphans: 1"><span style="background-color: rgb(186, 186, 255); font-family: monospace; font-weight: bold"><span style="font-family: Open Sans, Segoe UI, Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #2a212d; ">Mention either it&#39;s an informal warning or that the user was assessed a strike. Mention the strike number it is. If it&#39;s the third, sixth, or nineth strike, mention so and state the additional punishment they have earned as a result. If it is not the 3rd / 6th / 9th strike, tell them that at the (closest) strike, they will receive 14-day probation (3rd strike), 30-day suspension (6th strike), or consideration for permanent ban (9th strike).</span></span></p>
	</li>
	<li>
