	</li>
	<li>
	<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; orphans: 1"><span style="background-color: rgb(186, 186, 255); font-family: monospace; font-weight: bold"><span style="font-family: Open Sans, Segoe UI, Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #2a212d; ">If they have been silenced from a forum topic or a forum, state so and state for how long.</span></span></p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; orphans: 1"><span style="background-color: rgb(186, 186, 255); font-family: monospace; font-weight: bold"><span style="font-family: Open Sans, Segoe UI, Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #2a212d; ">If they are being put in probation, state how long and that during probation they cannot host any radio shows and all content submitted is subject to moderator approval.</span></span></p>
	</li>
	<li>
	<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; orphans: 1"><span style="background-color: rgb(186, 186, 255); font-family: monospace; font-weight: bold"><span style="font-family: Open Sans, Segoe UI, Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #2a212d; ">If they are being suspended, state the minimum suspension time and that after this time has passed, that during this time they cannot log in nor do their radio shows if they have any, and that they must appeal the suspension in order for it to be lifted. Describe what they need to do to appeal it&hellip; whatever you think is fitting&hellip; but be sure to also include that they have to write an apology letter in their appeal.</span></span></p>
