<span style="font-family: Open Sans, Segoe UI, Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #2a212d; ">I am Lovinity, the founder of The Lovinity Community. This is a notice of violation of our website rules, located at http://lovinity.org/pg/rules . A forum post was reported to us that indicated discussion of illegal activity with regards to planning to start a naked protest. The forum with the violating content can be found at (forum doesn&#39;t exist, so I can&#39;t put a link here). This post is in violation of section 8.8 of our rules, which states &quot;</span>&nbsp;You may not publish content that constitutes an incitement to commit a crime, instructions for the commission of a crime, nor the promotion of criminal activity.&quot; The Lovinity Community does not, in any way, condone nor support illegal activity, and therefore we forbid discussion of such.<br />
<br />
<span style="font-family: Open Sans, Segoe UI, Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #2a212d; ">In an attempt to promote corrective behaviour and to keep our website safe, The following disciplinary actions have been assessed as a result of your violation:</span></span></p>
<span style="background-color: rgb(186, 186, 255); font-family: monospace; font-weight: bold"> </span>

