<p style="orphans: 1"><span style="background-color: rgb(186, 186, 255); font-family: monospace; font-weight: bold"><span style="font-family: Open Sans, Segoe UI, Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #2a212d; ">During your suspension, you will not be able to log in to your account nor host any radio shows. Please be aware that a suspension is not lifted until you appeal it. You must wait 44 days from today before you can appeal your suspension. After that time, you will need to create a DA appeal support ticket at our home page -&gt; support ticket. In your appeal, you will need to write a letter of apology to staff. The letter must demonstrate that you are truly sorry for what you&#39;ve done, that you understand fully what you&#39;ve done, what you&#39;ve learned from your suspension, how you&#39;ll behave differently when let back on site, and that you will not do it again. The letter will be reviewed by staff and will determine if you&#39;re ready to have your suspension lifted. If you&#39;re not ready, the suspension will be extended, but you can try appealing it again after the time expires. If you are ready, you&#39;ll be allowed back on site with 30-day probation. During the 30-day probation period, all content you submit must be approved by staff before it is displayed.</span><br />
<br />
<span style="font-family: Open Sans, Segoe UI, Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #2a212d; ">If you feel this Disciplinary action is incorrect or unfair, please file a DA appeal by going to our home page and clicking Support Tickets on the left.&nbsp;When filing an appeal to appeal the discipline as a whole, include proof / evidence / justification as to why the issued discipline was unfair or unjust. The appeal will then be reviewed by the moderation team and a final decision will be made, which cannot be appealed again. Please note apologies are NOT acceptable forms of discipline appeal.&nbsp;If you are in favor, we will modify our disciplinary actions as needed.</span><br />
<br />
<span style="font-family: Open Sans, Segoe UI, Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color: #2a212d; ">Thank you for reading this message and understanding. We also appreciate your cooperation.</span></span></p>[/semihtml]